complete DevOps demo project

Goal:
Deploy a simple Spring Boot Java app to AWS EKS using Jenkins CI/CD.

Constraints:
- DO NOT install anything on local machine
- Everything must run on a single EC2 instance (Jenkins, Maven, Docker)
- Kubernetes cluster must be AWS EKS

Requirements:
1. Spring Boot app (simple REST API)
2. Dockerfile for app
3. Jenkins setup on EC2
4. Jenkins pipeline (Declarative):
   - Pull code from Git
   - Build using Maven
   - Build Docker image
   - Push to ECR
   - Deploy to EKS using kubectl
5. Kubernetes manifests:
   - Deployment
   - Service (LoadBalancer)
6. One single shell script to install on EC2:
   - Java
   - Jenkins
   - Maven
   - Docker
   - AWS CLI
   - kubectl
   - eksctl
7. IAM roles and permissions needed
8. ECR repo creation steps

Output format:
- Project folder structure
- All code files
- Jenkinsfile
- install.sh script
- Kubernetes YAMLs

Also include:
A detailed step-by-step instructor guide explaining:
- EC2 setup
- Running install script
- Creating EKS cluster
- Connecting Jenkins to EKS
- Running pipeline
- Verifying deployment

Keep it simple, beginner-friendly, and production-realistic.